# No Code Repetition (DRY)

Do not repeat the same or similar code in multiple places. Extract shared logic into:

- **Callback functions** – parameterized logic used in multiple handlers
- **Reusable components** – repeated UI patterns
- **Utility functions** – shared logic across modules
- **Custom hooks** – repeated React state or side-effect logic
- **Shared constants/types** – repeated values or type definitions

When you notice similar code in 2+ places, refactor to a single reusable abstraction.

## Examples

### Repeated logic → utility function

```typescript
// BAD – same validation logic duplicated
function createUser(data) {
  if (!data.email?.includes("@")) throw new Error("Invalid email");
  if (data.name?.length < 2) throw new Error("Name too short");
  // ...
}
function updateUser(data) {
  if (!data.email?.includes("@")) throw new Error("Invalid email");
  if (data.name?.length < 2) throw new Error("Name too short");
  // ...
}

// GOOD – shared validation extracted
function validateUserInput(data) {
  if (!data.email?.includes("@")) throw new Error("Invalid email");
  if (data.name?.length < 2) throw new Error("Name too short");
}
function createUser(data) {
  validateUserInput(data);
  // ...
}
function updateUser(data) {
  validateUserInput(data);
  // ...
}
```

### Repeated UI → reusable component

```tsx
// BAD – same card markup repeated
<Card className="p-4 border rounded">
  <h3>{item.title}</h3>
  <p>{item.description}</p>
</Card>
// ... same structure elsewhere

// GOOD – extract ItemCard component
<ItemCard item={item} />
```
